Yeah. well my father told me
that's how it starts.

229
00:14:35.459 --> 00:14:36.960
Get the fuck out of our neighborhood.

230
00:14:37.002 --> 00:14:38.545
you fucking niggers!

231
00:14:38.587 --> 00:14:40.923
Go back to Australia where you came from!

232
00:14:40.964 --> 00:14:42.716
You're lucky you're on that bus!

233
00:14:42.758 --> 00:14:45.094
Ha! You missed me!

234
00:14:45.135 --> 00:14:46.220
(BOYS SHOUTING)

235
00:14:46.261 --> 00:14:47.554
Stay out of our neighborhood.

236
00:14:47.596 --> 00:14:48.680
(SHARP WHISTLE)

237
00:14:54.269 --> 00:14:55.437
Why?

238
00:14:58.690 --> 00:14:59.691
Ah. shit.

239
00:15:07.783 --> 00:15:10.786
You don't fucking stop.
Get the fuck outta here!

240
00:15:12.037 --> 00:15:14.248
Nobody's cooler than you. Sonny.

241
00:15:18.085 --> 00:15:19.878
MAN 1: What the fuck is wrong with you?

242
00:15:19.920 --> 00:15:21.713
MAN 2: What you doin'?

243
00:15:21.755 --> 00:15:23.483
-MAN 1: Fuck you. you freehole!
-MAN 2: Fuck you. you scumbag!

244
00:15:23.507 --> 00:15:24.967
MAN 1: You're a real motherfucker!

245
00:15:25.008 --> 00:15:26.218
I'll bust your fucking head!

246
00:15:28.554 --> 00:15:30.764
I'm gonna bust your fucking head!

247
00:15:30.806 --> 00:15:32.641
(GUNSHOTS)

248
00:15:39.648 --> 00:15:40.774
SONNY: Hold on here.

249
00:15:41.483 --> 00:15:42.734
(GUNSHOTS)

250
00:15:42.776 --> 00:15:44.445
(WHISPERS) Sonny. give me the gun!

251
00:15:44.486 --> 00:15:46.530
Get the fucking car!
Move the fucking car!

252
00:15:48.740 --> 00:15:49.825
Come on!

253
00:15:50.868 --> 00:15:52.494
(ENGINE REVVING)

254
00:15:59.793 --> 00:16:02.796
<i>When Sonny looked at me
for the first time. I went deaf.</i>

255
00:16:02.838 --> 00:16:05.048
<i>I couldn't hear.</i>

256
00:16:05.090 --> 00:16:07.134
<i>All I could see was Sonny
with the gun in his hand.</i>

257
00:16:11.138 --> 00:16:13.140
(CHURCH BELLS IN DISTANCE)

258
00:16:29.490 --> 00:16:30.616
Dad!

259
00:16:33.368 --> 00:16:34.703
What happened? Is he all right?

260
00:16:34.745 --> 00:16:36.497
Dad. it was just a parking space.

261
00:16:36.538 --> 00:16:37.873
CALOGERO: You don't understand!

262
00:16:37.915 --> 00:16:39.875
Is he all right? Baby. are you OK?

263
00:16:39.917 --> 00:16:41.251
He's all right. Let's go inside.

264
00:16:41.293 --> 00:16:43.170
-What happened?
-I'm OK. Mom. I'm OK.

265
00:16:43.212 --> 00:16:46.340
-Oh my god. I got so scared.
-I'm OK. Mom.

266
00:16:49.551 --> 00:16:51.029
CALOGERO: You don't understand. Dad.

267
00:16:51.053 --> 00:16:52.846
They were fighting over a
parking space.

268
00:16:52.888 --> 00:16:54.181
ROSINA: Over a parking space?

269
00:16:54.223 --> 00:16:55.283
Over a parking space. Daddy.
Why?

270
00:16:55.307 --> 00:16:56.767
It wasn't over a parking space.

271
00:16:56.808 --> 00:16:58.119
They just met at the wrong time
in their lives.

272
00:16:58.143 --> 00:16:59.811
Well. what kind of answer is that?

273
00:16:59.853 --> 00:17:01.706
-He could've gotten killed!
-Just leave it alone.

274
00:17:01.730 --> 00:17:03.082
Let's mind our own business.
He's OK. That's the main thing.

275
00:17:03.106 --> 00:17:04.209
I can't believe somebody would do this.

276
00:17:04.233 --> 00:17:05.442
(KNOCKING)

277
00:17:08.654 --> 00:17:10.155
Who is it?

278
00:17:10.197 --> 00:17:12.037
BELSIK: Police.
Is this the Anello residence?

279
00:17:14.201 --> 00:17:15.369
Yeah. Can I help you?

280
00:17:15.410 --> 00:17:16.787
BELSIK: Look. we're detectives.

281
00:17:16.828 --> 00:17:19.122
We'd like to ask you some questions.

282
00:17:19.164 --> 00:17:21.667
-About what?
-BELSIK: Just open the door!

283
00:17:28.257 --> 00:17:30.008
How you doing? OK. good.

284
00:17:30.050 --> 00:17:32.153
I'm Detective Belsik. this is my
partner. Detective Vella.

285
00:17:32.177 --> 00:17:34.721
Hello. son.
How you doing. ma'am?

286
00:17:34.763 --> 00:17:36.598
We'd like to ask your son
a few questions.

287
00:17:36.640 --> 00:17:38.433
About what?

288
00:17:38.475 --> 00:17:39.744
There was a shooting in front of
the building a little while ago.

289
00:17:39.768 --> 00:17:40.828
and we believe your son was there.

290
00:17:40.852 --> 00:17:42.312
Really?

291
00:17:42.354 --> 00:17:44.064
Well. he don't know nothing about that.

292
00:17:44.106 --> 00:17:45.625
Well. we feel he does.
There were people who saw him.

293
00:17:45.649 --> 00:17:47.317
Well they're wrong.
He don't know nothing.

294
00:17:47.359 --> 00:17:49.170
Listen. Mr. Anello. We can do
things the nice way

295
00:17:49.194 --> 00:17:51.029
or we can do things the hard way. all right?

296
00:17:51.071 --> 00:17:52.674
-We can go down to headquarters.
-I don't care what way you do.

297
00:17:52.698 --> 00:17:54.950
-He don't know nothing.
-Daddy. I know everything.

298
00:17:57.953 --> 00:17:59.788
(SHALLOW LAUGH)

299
00:17:59.830 --> 00:18:01.516
Kids. Sometimes. you know. they
make believe they see things.

300
00:18:01.540 --> 00:18:03.208
We didn't pick your name out of a hat.

301
00:18:03.250 --> 00:18:05.919
We know your son was down there.
So. come on. let's go.

302
00:18:07.754 --> 00:18:10.507
Son. listen. Here's what I'd
like you to do for us.

303
00:18:10.549 --> 00:18:11.985
I'd like you to take a walk downstairs

304
00:18:12.009 --> 00:18:13.427
with us and your father.

305
00:18:13.468 --> 00:18:15.429
We have some people down there.

306
00:18:15.470 --> 00:18:17.639
All I want you to do is pick out
the person you saw

307
00:18:17.681 --> 00:18:20.976
with the gun in his hand.
That's it.

308
00:18:21.018 --> 00:18:22.436
You think you can do that for us?

309
00:18:33.071 --> 00:18:35.282
-Yeah.
-Good.

310
00:18:35.324 --> 00:18:36.617
Come on. Let's take a walk.

311
00:18:36.658 --> 00:18:38.493
Mr. Anello. take a walk downstairs.

312
00:18:40.621 --> 00:18:42.080
We won't be long. Go ahead.

313
00:18:42.122 --> 00:18:43.457
Officer. is he gonna be OK?

314
00:18:43.498 --> 00:18:44.916
Everything's gonna be fine. dear.

315
00:18:44.958 --> 00:18:46.376
They'll be back in two minutes.

316
00:18:50.631 --> 00:18:52.966
(POLICE SIRENS IN DISTANCE)

317
00:18:55.093 --> 00:18:57.346
(PEOPLE MUMBLING)

318
00:19:09.358 --> 00:19:10.817
There's Lorenzo.

319
00:19:42.933 --> 00:19:44.017
Hey fellas. turn around.

320
00:19:47.437 --> 00:19:49.981
You two. take your hats off.

321
00:19:50.023 --> 00:19:53.735
Hey! Put your head up.
Straight ahead. Look this way.

322
00:19:54.611 --> 00:19:57.489
-Is that him?
-No.

323
00:20:03.745 --> 00:20:06.373
How about this guy?
Straight ahead. fella.

324
00:20:07.207 --> 00:20:08.875
-How about him?
-No.

325
00:20:10.752 --> 00:20:13.797
Straight ahead. you.
How about this guy.

326
00:20:16.091 --> 00:20:17.426
Give me an answer.

327
00:20:17.467 --> 00:20:19.386
-How about him?
-No.

328
00:20:23.515 --> 00:20:26.059
How about him? Is it this guy?

329
00:20:28.562 --> 00:20:29.730
Give me an answer.

330
00:20:31.314 --> 00:20:34.401
-No.
-OK.

331
00:20:35.152 --> 00:20:36.862
Hey! Put your eyes up!

332
00:20:38.947 --> 00:20:40.407
How about this guy?

333
00:20:44.411 --> 00:20:46.747
No? Let's go.

334
00:20:46.788 --> 00:20:48.957
Hey! Look straight ahead!
Over here.

335
00:20:51.251 --> 00:20:52.794
Look at me. That's it.

336
00:20:53.378 --> 00:20:54.755
Is it this guy?

337
00:20:56.631 --> 00:20:58.925
-How about this guy?
-No.

338
00:20:58.967 --> 00:21:03.722
OK. Look at this guy.
How about him?

339
00:21:04.681 --> 00:21:06.308
(CHURCH BELLS IN DISTANCE)

340
00:21:06.349 --> 00:21:08.643
Hey! Straight ahead!

341
00:21:10.187 --> 00:21:13.482
How about this guy? Is it him?

342
00:21:14.816 --> 00:21:19.070
(BELLS RINGING)

343
00:21:29.080 --> 00:21:30.081
Give me an answer.

344
00:21:33.418 --> 00:21:34.961
-No.
-You satisfied. Officer?

345
00:21:35.003 --> 00:21:36.314
-No. I'm not satisfied.
-He don't know.

346
00:21:36.338 --> 00:21:37.964
-He can't help you.
-Yeah. yeah.

347
00:21:38.006 --> 00:21:39.442
Your son doesn't know anything.
I know all about it.

348
00:21:39.466 --> 00:21:41.259
He said no. he can't help you.

349
00:21:41.301 --> 00:21:43.488
I'll tell you what. Take a walk.
Go ahead. go ahead. Take a walk.

350
00:21:43.512 --> 00:21:44.805
Come on. son. Let's go.

351
00:21:51.019 --> 00:21:52.705
All right. you guys
can breathe again. Beat it.

352
00:21:52.729 --> 00:21:54.189
Get outta here.
Get out of my sight.

353
00:21:55.816 --> 00:21:57.776
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

354
00:21:59.027 --> 00:22:00.671
We fooled them.
dad. we really fooled them.

355
00:22:00.695 --> 00:22:01.988
Yeah. we fooled them.

356
00:22:02.864 --> 00:22:04.616
I didn't rat. dad. I didn't rat.

357
00:22:05.367 --> 00:22:06.660
No. you didn't rat.

358
00:22:07.536 --> 00:22:09.788
I did a good thing. right?

359
00:22:09.830 --> 00:22:11.164
Yeah. you did a good thing.

360
00:22:11.206 --> 00:22:12.874
You did a good thing for a bad man.

361
00:22:14.876 --> 00:22:17.712
CALOGERO: <i>I did a good thing
for a bad man.</i>

362
00:22:17.754 --> 00:22:20.674
<i>I didn't understand that.
not at nine years old.</i>

363
00:22:21.383 --> 00:22:23.718
<i>All I knew was...</i>

364
00:22:23.760 --> 00:22:26.030
<i>a rat was the lowest thing one
could be in my neighborhood.</i>

365
00:22:26.054 --> 00:22:27.222
<i>And I didn't rat.</i>

366
00:22:31.226 --> 00:22:32.727
Hey.

367
00:22:43.321 --> 00:22:46.157
Daddy. why did you say I did
a good thing for a bad man?

368
00:22:48.368 --> 00:22:51.037
Because sometimes in life you
gotta do certain things that you

369
00:22:51.079 --> 00:22:53.540
gotta do.
even though they're not right.

370
00:22:54.791 --> 00:22:56.668
Do you understand what I'm saying?

371
00:22:57.544 --> 00:22:59.170
No. It's just that...

372
00:22:59.212 --> 00:23:03.133
I thought I did the right thing.
Now I'm not sure I did.

373
00:23:03.174 --> 00:23:04.676
You did do the right thing.

374
00:23:04.718 --> 00:23:06.845
And when you get older.
you'll understand why.

375
00:23:06.887 --> 00:23:09.180
Your mother and I love you very.
very much.

376
00:23:14.769 --> 00:23:16.897
Tomorrow you take a ride
on the bus with me. OK?

377
00:23:17.606 --> 00:23:19.524
(SLOW JAZZ MUSIC)

378
00:23:21.192 --> 00:23:24.571
CALOGERO: <i>City Island was the
last stop on my father's route.</i>

379
00:23:24.613 --> 00:23:27.115
<i>It was one of our favorite places.</i>

380
00:23:27.157 --> 00:23:30.410
<i>It was like going on a vacation for a day.</i>

381
00:23:30.452 --> 00:23:32.120
<i>My dad would listen to his jazz</i>

382
00:23:32.162 --> 00:23:33.482
<i>and we would talk about baseball.</i>

383
00:23:39.336 --> 00:23:41.212
Dad. can I have an ice cream?

384
00:23:41.254 --> 00:23:44.090
We do our job first. and then
I'll get you an ice cream.

385
00:23:44.132 --> 00:23:45.592
-OK?
-OK. pop.

386
00:23:51.222 --> 00:23:52.933
Let's play the game. Dad.

387
00:23:52.974 --> 00:23:54.726
OK. let's see how good you are today.

388
00:23:54.768 --> 00:23:56.811
Who was the last player
to win the Triple Crown?

389
00:23:56.853 --> 00:24:00.398
Mickey Mantle.
Batting average.353.

390
00:24:00.440 --> 00:24:04.319
RBIs. 130. Home runs. 52.

391
00:24:05.236 --> 00:24:06.738
That's pretty good. son.

392
00:24:06.780 --> 00:24:08.341
He's the best ballplayer
that ever lived. Dad.

393
00:24:08.365 --> 00:24:10.116
Joe D's the greatest ballplayer.

394
00:24:11.826 --> 00:24:14.955
The Yankee Clipper.
56-game hitting streak.

395
00:24:14.996 --> 00:24:17.123
-That's right.
-Nobody beat that. Right. dad?

396
00:24:17.165 --> 00:24:19.793
Nobody beat that. son.

397
00:24:19.834 --> 00:24:21.711
Do you know why Joe D. was so great?

398
00:24:21.753 --> 00:24:24.464
-Because he was Italian?
-Well. that's part of it.

399
00:24:24.506 --> 00:24:25.966
Then why?

400
00:24:26.007 --> 00:24:27.801
Because he had more talent
than anybody.

401
00:24:27.842 --> 00:24:29.594
-Talent?
-That's right.

402
00:24:30.762 --> 00:24:32.764
Do I have talent. Dad?

403
00:24:32.806 --> 00:24:34.182
Of course you have talent.

404
00:24:34.224 --> 00:24:35.934
You got all the talent in the world.

405
00:24:35.976 --> 00:24:38.061
Can I be a baseball player?

406
00:24:38.103 --> 00:24:40.230
You can be anything you wanna be.

407
00:24:40.271 --> 00:24:43.733
Remember. the saddest thing
in life is wasted talent.

408
00:24:43.775 --> 00:24:45.610
You could have all the talent in the world.

409
00:24:45.652 --> 00:24:47.588
but if you don't do the right
thing. then nothing happens.

410
00:24:47.612 --> 00:24:50.949
But when you do right. guess
what. good things happen.

411
00:24:50.991 --> 00:24:53.243
-You hear me?
-You're right.

412
00:24:53.284 --> 00:24:55.829
-Let's go for that ice cream.
-Yeah. good.

413
00:24:57.205 --> 00:24:58.999
I'm gonna shut the doors. right. Dad?

414
00:24:59.040 --> 00:25:00.291
Yeah.

415
00:25:03.378 --> 00:25:05.088
Ready? Watch it.

416
00:25:07.465 --> 00:25:09.676
-Got it?
-I got it.

417
00:25:11.553 --> 00:25:13.888
CALOGERO: <i>Wasted talent.</i>

418
00:25:13.930 --> 00:25:17.308
<i>That was something my father
would talk about all my life.</i>

419
00:25:17.350 --> 00:25:20.145
Come on. let's hurry. so we can
catch the start of the game.

420
00:25:20.186 --> 00:25:24.107
GAME ANNOUNCER: <i>36.683 here
to see the final game</i>

421
00:25:24.149 --> 00:25:26.151
<i>of the 60 Series.</i>

422
00:25:26.192 --> 00:25:28.278
<i>And what a ball game they're looking at.</i>

423
00:25:28.319 --> 00:25:31.531
<i>Moose Skowron. with that
infield hit deep to third...</i>

424
00:25:31.573 --> 00:25:35.368
<i>has picked up his twelfth
World Series base hit in 1960.</i>

425
00:25:40.123 --> 00:25:42.292
<i>Time called momentarily.
Blanchard's back...</i>

426
00:25:45.587 --> 00:25:46.755
Come on. Sonny. Give me...

427
00:25:51.468 --> 00:25:55.180
ANNOUNCER: <i>One out. unassisted.
to Nelson. to end the sixth.</i>

428
00:25:55.221 --> 00:25:59.434
<i>Southpaw hitter. And
Elroy Face staring down to his</i>

429
00:25:59.476 --> 00:26:01.478
<i>battery mate Hal Smith.</i>

430
00:26:01.519 --> 00:26:04.022
<i>Into the stretch now.
The little man sets.</i>

431
00:26:04.064 --> 00:26:05.857
<i>And here's the first one
coming to Blanchard.</i>

432
00:26:05.899 --> 00:26:07.734
<i>Outside and a ball.</i>

433
00:26:07.776 --> 00:26:09.444
(BUS BRAKING)

434
00:26:11.780 --> 00:26:14.365
-See you later. Pop.
-OK.

435
00:26:19.788 --> 00:26:22.916
Get right upstairs. son.
And watch the rest of the game.

436
00:26:22.957 --> 00:26:24.834
Get right upstairs.
no hanging out. son.

437
00:26:33.676 --> 00:26:35.637
Hey. Lorenzo. how you doing?

438
00:26:35.678 --> 00:26:37.430
Keep driving. I wanna talk to you.

439
00:26:39.891 --> 00:26:42.102
Your kid is a good kid. that kid.

440
00:26:42.644 --> 00:26:44.521
Thanks.

441
00:26:44.562 --> 00:26:46.248
Sonny really appreciates what
you and your son did for him.

442
00:26:46.272 --> 00:26:48.858
That's all right. I'm just glad
everything worked out.

443
00:26:48.900 --> 00:26:50.568
He'd like to do something for you.

444
00:26:50.610 --> 00:26:52.612
All you gotta do is drop some
numbers off for us.

445
00:26:52.654 --> 00:26:54.280
You're gonna get 150 dollars a week.

446
00:26:54.322 --> 00:26:56.116
Won't even have to get off the bus.

447
00:26:56.157 --> 00:26:58.201
Tell him I appreciate it.
but I got a city job.

448
00:26:58.243 --> 00:26:59.869
If I get pinched. I could lose it.

449
00:26:59.911 --> 00:27:01.347
-At least think about it.
-I just can't do it.

450
00:27:01.371 --> 00:27:04.124
-It's not for me.
-150 dollars a week.

451
00:27:04.165 --> 00:27:06.292
-You don't wanna think about it?
-I can't do it.

452
00:27:06.334 --> 00:27:08.670
It's just not for me.
I can't do it.

453
00:27:08.711 --> 00:27:10.755
Sonny's gonna be disappointed.

454
00:27:10.797 --> 00:27:12.149
But I'm gonna tell him what you said.

455
00:27:12.173 --> 00:27:14.300
-OK.
-Stop the bus here.

456
00:27:14.342 --> 00:27:15.385
I wanna get off.

457
00:27:24.727 --> 00:27:27.063
(BUS ENGINE REVVING)

458
00:27:34.279 --> 00:27:36.114
LORENZO: They offered me a job today.

459
00:27:36.156 --> 00:27:38.032
-ROSINA: Doing what?
-Numbers.

460
00:27:38.074 --> 00:27:40.177
All I gotta do is pick up
a piece of paper and drop it off

461
00:27:40.201 --> 00:27:42.871
on my round and they said
they'll give me 150 a week.

462
00:27:42.912 --> 00:27:44.831
150 a week? What did you say?

463
00:27:44.873 --> 00:27:46.166
What do you think I said?

464
00:27:46.207 --> 00:27:48.418
I told him to forget it.
It's not for me.

465
00:27:53.298 --> 00:27:55.341
What?

466
00:27:55.383 --> 00:27:59.512
I don't know. 150 dollars?
It's only numbers.

467
00:27:59.554 --> 00:28:02.932
-You think I should've took it.
-I don't know.

468
00:28:04.184 --> 00:28:05.518
Yeah. but. come on. you know...

469
00:28:05.560 --> 00:28:06.978
You get involved with those guys.

470
00:28:07.020 --> 00:28:08.540
next thing you know.
one. two. three...

471
00:28:09.439 --> 00:28:10.857
